                <title>btQuaternion njli::AbstractTransform::getRotation () const</title> <emphasis></emphasis>
                
<para>The four-component rotation vector specifies the direction of the rotation axis in the first three components and the angle of rotation (in radians) in the fourth. The default rotation is the zero vector, specifying no rotation. Rotation is applied relative to the node’s pivot property.</para>

<para>The rotation, eulerAngles, and orientation properties all affect the rotational aspect of its transform property. Any change to one of these properties is reflected in the others.</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Returns: </title>

<para>the Rotation for this instance. </para>
</formalpara>
</para>

